allowedMethods.description: One or more HTTP methods that you allow the origin to execute. Can be `GET`, `PUT`, `POST`, `DELETE` or `HEAD`.

allowedOrigins.description: One or more origins you want customers to be able to access the bucket from.

exposeHeaders.description: One or more headers in the response that you want customers to be able to access from their applications (for example, from a JavaScript `XMLHttpRequest` object).

maxAgeSeconds.description: Specifies time in seconds that browser can cache the response for a preflight request.
